<glossary>
<definition id="fs-id1172100771172">
<term>Feynman diagram</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1172100539097">space-time diagram that describes how particles move and interact</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1172100894095">
<term>quantum chromodynamics (QCD)</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1172100658697">theory that describes strong interactions between quarks</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1172098315425">
<term>quantum electrodynamics (QED)</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1172098524655">theory that describes the interaction of electrons with photons</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1172100585448">
<term>Standard Model</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1172098498799">model of particle interactions that contains the electroweak theory and quantum chromodynamics (QCD)</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1172100844901">
<term>virtual particle</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1172100771656">particle that exists for too short of time to be observable</meaning>
</definition>
</glossary>
